{"id": 7810, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "HL", "paper": "3", "year": "2019", "session": "19N", "subtopic": "1-3-reacting-masses-and-volumes", "title": "19N.3.HL.TZ0.8", "topic_id": "1", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">1.40 × 10<sup>−3</sup> g of NaOH (s) are dissolved in 250.0 cm<sup>3</sup> of 1.00 × 10<sup>−11</sup> mol dm<sup>−3</sup> Pb(OH)<sub>2</sub> (aq) solution.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Determine the change in lead ion concentration in the solution, using section 32 of the data booklet.</span></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">«[OH<sup>−</sup>] =<span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{1.40 \\times {{10}^{ - 3}}{\\text{g}}}}{{40.00{\\text{ g mo}}{{\\text{l}}^{ - 1}} \\times 0.2500{\\text{ d}}{{\\text{m}}^3}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mn>1.40</mn> <mo>×</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mn>10</mn> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>3</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mrow> <mtext>g</mtext> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mn>40.00</mn> <mrow> <mtext> g mo</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>l</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>−</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> <mo>×</mo> <mn>0.2500</mn> <mrow> <mtext> d</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mtext>m</mtext> </mrow> <mn>3</mn> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span> =» 1.40 × 10<sup>−4</sup> «mol dm<sup>−3</sup>» ✔</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">«[OH<sup>−</sup>] from dissolved Pb(OH)<sub>2</sub> is negligible»</span></span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">NOTE: Accept «ratio </span></span></em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{{{\\left[ {P{b^{2 + }}} \\right]}_{initial}}}}{{{{\\left[ {P{b^{2 + }}} \\right]}_{final}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>[</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mrow> <msup> <mi>b</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>]</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mi>n</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>t</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>a</mi> <mi>l</mi> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>[</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mrow> <msup> <mi>b</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>]</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>n</mi> <mi>a</mi> <mi>l</mi> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span> <em>=» 13.7 </em><em><strong>OR  </strong>«ratio </em><span class=\"mjpage\"><math alttext=\"\\frac{{{{\\left[ {P{b^{2 + }}} \\right]}_{final}}}}{{{{\\left[ {P{b^{2 + }}} \\right]}_{initial}}}}\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mfrac> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>[</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mrow> <msup> <mi>b</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>]</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>n</mi> <mi>a</mi> <mi>l</mi> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mrow> <msub> <mrow> <mrow> <mo>[</mo> <mrow> <mi>P</mi> <mrow> <msup> <mi>b</mi> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>+</mo> </mrow> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>]</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mrow> <mi>i</mi> <mi>n</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>t</mi> <mi>i</mi> <mi>a</mi> <mi>l</mi> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> </mfrac> </math></span> <em>=» 0.0730 for M4.</em></span></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><em>K</em><sub>sp</sub> = [Pb<sup>2+</sup>][OH<sup>−</sup>]<sup>2</sup><br/><em><strong>OR<br/></strong></em>1.43 × 10<sup>−20</sup> = [Pb<sup>2+</sup>] × (1.40 × 10<sup>−4</sup>)<sup>2</sup> ✔</span></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">[Pb<sup>2+</sup>]<sub>final</sub> = 7.30 × 10<sup>−13</sup> «mol dm<sup>−3</sup>» ✔</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">NOTE: Award <strong>[4]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></span></span></span></em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">«change in [Pb<sup>2+</sup>] = 1.00 × 10<sup>−11</sup> − 7.30 × 10<sup>−13</sup> =» 9.27 × 10<sup>−12</sup> «mol dm<sup>−3</sup>» ✔</span></span></span></span></span></p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"> NOTE: Award<strong> [3]</strong> for correct [Pb<sup>2+</sup>]<sub>final</sub>.</span></span></span></span></span></em></p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n[N/A]\n</div>"}